## Why this fixes your issue

Right now:

* build publishes `DatabaseProjectAlterna_Telecom.dacpac`
* deploy searches for `database.dacpac`

So preview can show the new table, while deploy can miss it because it is not using the same filename path.

After this change:

* build and deploy agree on the exact DACPAC filename
* the download folder is cleaned each time
* the deployed DACPAC is deterministic

The current build template already supports custom `dacpacFileName`, while the deploy template is still hardcoded to `database.dacpac`, which is exactly the mismatch you’re fixing here.  

The only remaining update after this is to make your **preview pipeline/template** also accept `dacpacFileName`, so preview and deploy use the exact same file-selection rule.
